claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A flowchart diagram showing the selection and attrition of study participants aged 18–64 years who received either a recombinant influenza vaccine or a standard-dose vaccine across multiple influenza seasons, detailing numbers excluded for membership status, inpatient vaccinations, timing outside eligible dates, missing facility identifiers, unassigned propensity scores, and final cohort counts by age group. The image does not support the claim because it presents only participant flow and cohort selection data without any information on antigenic match to WHO- or FDA-selected flu strains. Note: The figure is clear and legible but contains no data on strain matching or antigenic analyses.
